The COVID-19 epidemic continues to spread.

As of 2400 hours on January 20,291 confirmed cases of COVID-19 pneumonia had been reported, including 270 in Hubei Province, five in Beijing, 14 in Guangdong Province and two in Shanghai, according to the National Health and Construction Commission, a total of 54 suspected cases were reported in 14 provinces including Sichuan and Yunnan.

As of 2400 hours on January 20,2020, the number of COVID-19 pneumonia deaths had increased to six, Zhou Xianwang, Wuhan's mayor, told CCTV.

Wuhan has stepped up prevention and control measures to curb the spread of COVID-19 pneumonia, measures have been taken to strengthen the control of people going in and out of Wuhan, establish epidemic prevention and control headquarters, and postpone the 2020 Spring Festival cultural tourism benefit activities.

The COVID-19 epidemic continues to spread.

As of 2400 hours on January 20,291 confirmed cases of COVID-19 pneumonia had been reported, including 270 in Hubei Province, five in Beijing, 14 in Guangdong Province and two in Shanghai, according to the National Health and Construction Commission, a total of 54 suspected cases were reported in 14 provinces including Sichuan and Yunnan.

As of 2400 hours on January 20,2020, the number of COVID-19 pneumonia deaths had increased to six, Zhou Xianwang, Wuhan's mayor, told CCTV.

Wuhan has stepped up prevention and control measures to curb the spread of COVID-19 pneumonia, measures have been taken to strengthen the control of people going in and out of Wuhan, establish epidemic prevention and control headquarters, and postpone the 2020 Spring Festival cultural tourism benefit activities.

At around 1600 hours today, a reporter from Hsinking daily visited the South China Seafood Wholesale Market in Jianghan District, Wuhan. He found that the scene was still under control. About 100 traders from the wholesale market gathered at the scene and queued up to receive government subsidies.

Focus on Wuhan

South China Seafood Market remains closed as traders line up for government subsidies

On the afternoon of January 21, Wuhan announced that it would continue to tighten control over the south China Seafood Wholesale Market after it closed, controlling the market and its surrounding entrances and exits 24 hours a day. We will strengthen the investigation of agricultural (collective) markets and various business places, carry out hygiene and epidemiological investigations, centralize isolation and treatment of cases found, and carry out medical observation on close contacts.

A field visit by a reporter from the Hsinking daily found that since the closure on January 1, the south China seafood market has remained closed, with all businesses in the eastern and western districts closed and businesses in the surrounding districts affected. Some traders who had operated in the market said that in order to maintain the supply of their old customers, they had now moved to other wholesale markets for distribution.

HSINKING news reporters learned from a number of police at the scene that after the Wuhan Municipal Health and Health Commission issued a report that the outbreak was related to the south China Seafood Wholesale Market, multiple departments conducted control over the market and banned others from entering, except for relevant staff. At present, the epidemic situation is on the rise. In order to reduce the economic losses of the merchants in the market, the local government has set up subsidy points under the offices outside the market.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At around 16:00 p.m. on January 21, the closed south China Seafood Wholesale Market in Wuhan. Photographer / Beijing News Reporter, you Tian Yi

A police officer at the scene who led businesses to line up said, "The source of the infection can not be determined and it came from nowhere, so everything from the shops in the market can not be sent out. The government subsidises the shops, with each household receiving about 10,000 yuan. "

HSINKING newspaper reporters found at the scene that under the coordination of the police and the security personnel at the scene, nearly 100 merchants lined up with the data to go to the temporary subsidy point and register their personal information. In order to prevent the spread of the epidemic, the police 24-hour duty to the south China seafood wholesale market around the epidemic prevention work.

At present, the South China Seafood Wholesale Market on the west side of the business door closed, closed, and pulled up the cordon. There are health department staff wearing protective clothing on the spot, the sale of fresh products to the merchants for disinfection and other epidemic prevention work.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
At about 1600 hours on January 21,50 meters west of the South China Seafood Wholesale Market in Wuhan, epidemic prevention workers inspected a fresh-meat vendor. Photographer / Beijing News, you Tian Yi

The stall involved in "popular animal game" has been closed

Recently, a south China Seafood Market in Wuhan Stores "Mass Livestock Game" sales picture widely circulated.

According to photos posted on the Internet, the farm sells 42 kinds of game, including bamboo rats, dog badgers, pig badgers, civet cats, foxes, Koalas, peacocks and wild geese, all of which can be butchered alive, frozen and delivered to homes.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The price list of "mass animal husbandry and Venison" spread on the Internet.

A market female shop owner told reporters that he had been to the "mass livestock" shop, the shop to sell mutton and other common meat-based. Another male shop owner said the market closed before the "general livestock" has been normal business, as far as he knows, the store does sell game.

According to public information, there are stalls legally selling wild animals in the south China market. On the morning of September 25,2019, the market supervision authorities at the two levels in the city of Wuhan, in conjunction with the municipal forestry and forest public security authorities, launched a special operation to regulate the wild animal market, according to the news released by the market supervision authority of the city of Wuhan, in the South China Seafood Wholesale Market, law enforcement officers at the city level and at the city level conducted a carpet inspection of nearly eight businesses selling animals such as tiger frogs, snakes and hedgehogs, and checked their wildlife business license approval documents and business licenses one by one, the management of unapproved wild animals shall be strictly prohibited.

South China market, a shop owner surnamed Li told reporters that the market to sell wild animals stalls concentrated in the Western central corridor, "secretly sell that how much is there. "

Officials from the China Wildlife Conservation Association said that if the animals were sold illegally, there would be doubts about the source of the channels and possible illegal activities such as illegal hunting. Some businesses may have violated the rules by not handling the relevant business use license and breeding license, whether the sale of wild animals has been tested by the regular quarantine system, and whether they have the permission of the relevant health and quarantine departments, there's no way of knowing.

Takatomi, director of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention and a member of the high level expert panel of the Covid-19, said yesterday that the source of the virus had been inferred from the south China Seafood Market, wildlife plays a key role in this. Academician Zhong Nanshan, head of the High Level Expert Group of the National Health Commission, also pointed out during the live broadcast on CCTV that it was not clear what kind of animal the virus originated from. From the epidemiological investigation, the virus from the wild animals, more likely is the bamboo rat, badger and so on.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On January 21, Wuhan Railway Station Entrance Gate, set up infrared thermometer, according to the staff, the total distribution of this instrument station has 16. Photographer / Beijing News, you Tian Yi

The railway station is equipped with a temperature measuring instrument to focus on the monitoring of heating passengers

At 2200 hours on the night of January 20, the Hankou Railway Station, less than a kilometer from the south China seafood market, was still crowded. At least four infrared thermometers have been installed at the south entrance of the Hankou Railway Station station to check the body temperature of passengers leaving the Han Dynasty, according to a Hsinking newspaper reporter at the scene. According to the staff, passengers'body temperatures will be checked at the station's entrances and exits, and passengers with temperatures above 38 degrees Celsius will be subjected to further tests and hospitals will be notified if necessary.

HSINKING newspaper reporters in Wuhan high-speed Railway Station also saw the installation of infrared thermometer, check the temperature of passengers entering and leaving the station.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan Railway Station, January 21, staff with a temperature detector through the arrival gate machine temperature. Photographer / Beijing News, you Tian Yi

It is understood that since January 14, Wuhan in the airport, railway stations, long-distance bus stations, passenger terminals, the rapid installation of infrared thermometer 35, equipped with hand-held infrared thermometer more than 300, and gradually increase the strength of the equipment.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan Railway Station on January 21, staff through the instrument to detect the temperature of passengers. Photographer / Beijing News, you Tian Yi

Sales of face masks around the Hankou Railway Station have soared

On January 20, a reporter from the Beijing News visited a number of supermarkets around the Hankou Railway Station and learned that sales of disposable masks had surged in a short period of time, with most of the buyers being foreign tourists arriving in Wuhan.

A supermarket owner showed reporters ordinary disposable masks and cotton masks on sale in the store. "The disposable masks cost 8 yuan for 10 pieces, and today they sold for more than 200 yuan in one day. " He said there were many confirmed cases reported in the news these two days, a lot more people come to buy masks.

Another supermarket owner told the reporter that disposable masks sold more than 100 in one day, and the buyers also had local residents, "The Hankou Railway Station is very close to the south China Seafood Market, and we don't want it to get infected, " said a reporter who bought a bag of disposable surgical masks from a snack bar near the entrance to the station, "More than a dozen bags have been sold out today, and now we can't get any more, " said the boss.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
On January 21, passengers on the platform. Photographer / Beijing News Reporter, Li Kaixiang

But not many Wuhan residents wear masks outside the Hankou Railway Station. A female university student at Wuhan's Wenhua College told the reporter that she had just returned from an event in Changsha, but did not wear a mask. "We had been warned by our school counselor not to go in crowded places and to wear masks when we went out, but it didn't feel that serious and we didn't always wear masks when we went out. "

On the evening of January 20, Zhong Nanshan, a member of the Chinese Academy of Engineering and the head of the High Level Expert Group of the COVID-19, said there was human to human transmission of the pneumonia. The reporter learned that a manufacturer has made it clear that its production of medical mask priority supply to Wuhan, many dealers have moved to Wuhan mask inventory.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Mask-wearing crew member of HNA. Photo provided by Hainan Airlines

HNA, hna: flight attendants can wear masks when flying to Wuhan

According to Civil Aviation Administration of China News from official website, on January 21, the Civil Aviation Administration issued a notice requiring all transport airlines to attach great importance to passenger service while doing a good job in the prevention and control of the pneumonia epidemic caused by COVID-19 infection, for those passengers who have purchased tickets for Wuhan Flight, the airline shall handle the refund request free of charge.

All units of the Civil Aviation System will do their best to prevent and control the epidemic in the civil aviation field, ensure that air transport work will be carried out in an orderly manner during the Spring Festival travel period, and reduce the risk of civil aviation passengers and employees being infected with the epidemic, to minimize the spread of the disease by aircraft.

Hsinking today learned from the staff of Hainan Airlines and Chongqing Airlines that, under the influence of the COVID-19, flight attendants will be allowed to wear face masks throughout the flight.

Chongqing Airlines introduced several flight attendants, the company on duty in the morning issued a notice that, from now on, flight attendants in Wuhan can wear masks throughout the flight.

Shen Yue (not her real name) , a flight attendant at Chongqing Airlines, told the Beijing News that as a flight attendant, it is impossible to avoid high-frequency, high-density close contact with passengers while flying, and the cabin is a relatively closed space. If there are passengers carrying the virus in the cabin, flight attendants are vulnerable.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The purser shows how to put on a mask properly. Hainan Airlines

In addition, at about 18:00 today, the reporter of the Hsinking daily learned from Hainan Airlines that hna has formulated a plan to prevent and control COVID-19 pneumonia.

A staff member of Hna told the Beijing News that recently, it was during the spring travel peak, personnel frequent round-trip, and coincided with the winter and spring respiratory infectious disease season. From now on, for flights through Wuhan, all crew members must wear masks. If passengers have cough, fever or other suspected symptoms during the flight, the flight attendants will take the initiative to provide masks and ask passengers to wear them.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Aeromedical demonstration on how to wear a mask correctly. Hainan Airlines

Expert: "Super Spreaders are likely to have emerged"

At about midnight today, World Health Organization spokesman Tarik Jasarevic told the Beijing News about the COVID-192019 ncov pneumonia outbreak, according to the latest information and analysis received by World Health Organization's Organization, there is evidence of limited human-to-human transmission, "consistent with the experience of other respiratory disease, particularly other coronavirus outbreaks, " but he stressed that there was no clear evidence of sustained human-to-human transmission. "We currently do not have enough information on the extent of human-to-human transmission, which is one of the issues being closely monitored by WHO. "

At about 1300 hours today, a reporter from the HSINKING newspaper received an updated statement from the WHO, saying that it was now possible to confirm from the latest information that at least some human-to-human transmission had occurred, as evidenced by the infection of medical staff. In addition, information on newly reported infections suggests that there may now be ongoing human-to-human transmission. "But we still need to do more analysis of epidemiological data to fully understand human-to-human transmission. "

The World Health Organization will hold an emergency committee meeting in Geneva on January 22, Director General Tan Desai said in a Jan. 20 tweet, the IHR provide for the determination of the circumstances caused by the COVID-19(2019-nCoV) .

Who director-general Tan Desai said the 22 meeting will assess whether the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic has reached the level of "a health emergency of international concern" and make recommendations on how to control the epidemic.

On January 20, Zhu Huachen, an associate professor at the public health of the University of Hong Kong who has long studied viral emerging infectious diseases, told the Beijing News that in general, if there are family clusters or hospital infections, or a community outbreak, there's a high probability of human-to-human transmission.

Zhu Huachen said that based on the information released so far, it can be determined that the COVID-19 can be passed from person to person, "The daughter among the Zhuhai patients, for example, has not seen successive generations of transmission, nor has there been a clear progression in the chain of transmission. "

There is also clear evidence of human-to-human transmission, with 14 health-care workers infected in one case. "In this case, it can be said that super-spreaders have probably already appeared, " Zhu explained. If a person directly infects many people (like 10 or more) , that person can be defined as a super-spreader, commonly known as the "poison king. ". But we can't rule out the possibility of a medical exchange.

Zhu Hua Chen expresses, still want to see whether can"continue to pass"next. In other words, "We need to see if these second-generation infections, are going to infect other people. We also need to see if these infected health care workers, were infected directly from the same patient, or if they were also infecting each other. " If there is a super-carrier, or there may be a large-scale outbreak, and has broken through the capacity of medical institutions, then this prevention and control will become very, very difficult.
